				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-12953024/scp-5900#post-4841953</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Fri, 11 Dec 2020 03:53:36 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>Gabriel McQueen</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>4558836</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>I feel like this hit in just the right place of &quot;this author knows more than me on a subject, but they don't want me to feel stupid because of that.&quot; I think it works so well because the focus is really on that emotional state of &quot;can't panic now, I've got too much to do,&quot; an experience I think most people have been through.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-12953024#post-4487544</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-12953024/scp-5900#post-4487544</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Sun, 02 Feb 2020 21:43:13 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>bibliolatry</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>3534136</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>Why would they attach their metaphysical stuff to the entire concept of KNOWLEDGE? That's literally fundamental to everything, period; it's a miracle it took someone this long to get pissed off at that and decide to sabotage them. Anyways, this is good. I got a bit freaked out when I saw SCUTTLE, though.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-12953024#post-4485467</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-12953024/scp-5900#post-4485467</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Fri, 31 Jan 2020 22:39:47 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>TL333s</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>1304786</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <blockquote> <p>Condition: clear skies. No forecasted storms for 6 hours.</p> </blockquote> <p>I laughed so hard at seeing this on the end of all those catastrophic notifications. Absolutely fantastic work of using technobabble in a way that didn't leave me, at least, feeling kept in the dark.</p> <p>I will say I'm not aware of any significance of the final note. I also kind of wish this had focused at all on, okay, the Foundation's monitoring network went down, we don't know why, <em>what did we miss seeing while it was out?</em></p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-12953024#post-4485298</guid>
				<title>+0</title>
