					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-12953024#post-4484472</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-12953024/scp-5900#post-4484472</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Fri, 31 Jan 2020 02:59:25 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>Lambda Fairy</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>1888005</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>Not sure how I feel about this. The hook is great, and the chat logs are more focused than before.</p> <p>But overall it feels like a lot of buildup to&#8230; something? The &quot;thaumaturgic JavaScript&quot; and time-travel networking are amusing, but they're never elaborated on beyond throwaway lines. And the appearance of the Serpent's Hand seems sudden—more to fulfill the requirement for an antagonist than a character in their own right.</p> <p>Neutral vote for now.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
